{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17486846","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17486846"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T02:46:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T02:46:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"188"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/188"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.63,0.02,0.11,0.21,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"188"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92387"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/188"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"188"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75692"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"581"},{"type":"tags","id":"1155"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"31557"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31558"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92387","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92387"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn otherwise well 47-year-old man presents with a painless swelling on the left side of his face. It has been growing slowly in size over the last eight months but does not trouble him unduly. Examination reveals a smooth, non-tender, mobile 3 cm mass in his cheek immediately in front of his ear. The skin moves freely over the swelling. He can blink both eyes and pout his lips without difficulty.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pleomorphic adenoma","Squamous cell carcinoma","Lymphoma","Warthin tumour","Adenocarcinoma"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anatomical position and the description of this swelling suggests that it almost certainly arises from the parotid gland. \u003Cstrong\u003EPleomorphic adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E are the most common tumour of the parotid gland. They are slow growing, smooth and mobile. \u003Cstrong\u003EWarthin tumours\u003C/strong\u003E are typically found in older men and are composed of multiple cysts and solid components and are usually found in the tail of the parotid gland. Any form of \u003Cstrong\u003Emalignancy\u003C/strong\u003E would likely have grown more rapidly - and may have lead to facial nerve involvement - which is not the case here.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Most parotid tumours are benign pleomorphic adenomas."],"references":["Gandolfi MM. Slattery W. Parotid Gland Tumors and the Facial Nerve. Otolaryngol Clin N Am 2016; 49:425-34."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75692"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"188"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75692","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/75692"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-17T15:16:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-17T15:16:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"188"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92387"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/35"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc43","name":"Otorhinolaryngology","synonyms":["ENT","HEENT"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:40:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type"